<richcontent TYPE="NOTE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      A business model is the operational and financial blueprint of a company&#8212;the design of how value is (created,) marketed, purchased, and delivered.
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      Edwards, Elizabeth (2010-12-15). Startup: The Complete Handbook for Launching a Company for Less (Kindle Location 397). Essential Books. Kindle Edition.
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      The business model needs to be profitable.
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
