<node COLOR="#990000" CREATED="1311605102155" ID="ID_1454424747" MODIFIED="1313205883342" TEXT="Convertible Debt">
<richcontent TYPE="NOTE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 18px; border-left-width: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 0px; background-repeat: repeat; border-color: black; border-right-width: 0px; color: rgb(71, 71, 71); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; background-position: initial initial; background-attachment: scroll; border-top-width: 0px; background-image: initial; line-height: 21px; vertical-align: baseline">
      Convertible debt has gained popularity in the last few years thanks to its success with Y Combinator startups and the fact that SV Angel and Yuri Miller have offered every Y Combinator startup<span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><a href="http://blogs.wsj.com/venturecapital/2011/02/01/y-combinators-paul-graham-on-the-150k-per-start-up-offer/" style="padding-bottom: 0px; margin-right: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; background-repeat: repeat; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 13px; border-color: black; border-right-width: 0px; color: rgb(30, 89, 142); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; background-position: initial initial; background-attachment: scroll; border-top-width: 0px; background-image: initial; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline" target="_blank"><font size="13px" color="rgb(30, 89, 142)">$150,000 in convertible debt</font></a>. When an investor offers a convertible note, the debt is converted to equity sometime in the future. This conversion is at a discount to the next funding round that you raise and typically has a cap, which means that if you raise a huge round, the debt investors have protected themselves from getting diluted.
    </p>
    <p style="padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 18px; border-left-width: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; font-size: 13px; background-repeat: repeat; margin-top: 0px; border-color: black; border-right-width: 0px; color: rgb(71, 71, 71); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; background-position: initial initial; background-attachment: scroll; border-top-width: 0px; background-image: initial; line-height: 21px; vertical-align: baseline">
      Convertible debt is popular because you don&#8217;t have to set a valuation. It is handled in the next round of financing. Also, convertible debt often requires less paperwork, which means you can keep your costs lower. A lot of investors don&#8217;t like convertible debt as much because the valuation of the company is an unknown at the time of investment.
    </p>
    <p style="padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 18px; border-left-width: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; font-size: 13px; background-repeat: repeat; margin-top: 0px; border-color: black; border-right-width: 0px; color: rgb(71, 71, 71); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; background-position: initial initial; background-attachment: scroll; border-top-width: 0px; background-image: initial; line-height: 21px; vertical-align: baseline">
      [ <a href="http://mashable.com/2011/06/10/raise-funds-startup/">http://mashable.com/2011/06/10/raise-funds-startup/</a>&#160;]
    </p>
    <p style="padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 18px; border-left-width: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; font-size: 13px; background-repeat: repeat; margin-top: 0px; border-color: black; border-right-width: 0px; color: rgb(71, 71, 71); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; background-position: initial initial; background-attachment: scroll; border-top-width: 0px; background-image: initial; line-height: 21px; vertical-align: baseline">
      
    </p>
    <p style="padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 18px; border-left-width: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; font-size: 13px; background-repeat: repeat; margin-top: 0px; border-color: black; border-right-width: 0px; color: rgb(71, 71, 71); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; background-position: initial initial; background-attachment: scroll; border-top-width: 0px; background-image: initial; line-height: 21px; vertical-align: baseline">
      
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
