<node COLOR="#990000" CREATED="1311605120438" ID="ID_506484605" MODIFIED="1313205883346" TEXT="Venture Debt">
<richcontent TYPE="NOTE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      Is it same as Venture funding?? If so then, read the following resource:
    </p>
    <p style="padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 18px; border-left-width: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 0px; background-repeat: repeat; border-color: black; border-right-width: 0px; color: rgb(71, 71, 71); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; background-position: initial initial; background-attachment: scroll; border-top-width: 0px; background-image: initial; line-height: 21px; vertical-align: baseline">
      A<span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><a href="http://www.usv.com/" style="padding-bottom: 0px; margin-right: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; background-repeat: repeat; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 13px; border-color: black; border-right-width: 0px; color: rgb(30, 89, 142); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; background-position: initial initial; background-attachment: scroll; border-top-width: 0px; background-image: initial; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline" target="_blank"><font size="13px" color="rgb(30, 89, 142)">startup venture fund</font></a><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span>pools investments from many limited partners and then manages that money by investing in startups that meet the objective of the fund. When you are looking to raise money from a venture fund, you often already have a working prototype and measurable traction in your business. The amount of money that these funds invest is typically a lot more than angel investments.
    </p>
    <p style="padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 18px; border-left-width: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; font-size: 13px; background-repeat: repeat; margin-top: 0px; border-color: black; border-right-width: 0px; color: rgb(71, 71, 71); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; background-position: initial initial; background-attachment: scroll; border-top-width: 0px; background-image: initial; line-height: 21px; vertical-align: baseline">
      Since these investment could be more than $1 million, the venture capitalist is often looking for a board seat to gain some control over their investment. Venture capitalists usually like investments in earlier stage companies to be in the 20% equity range. If you decide to try and get venture funding, it&#8217;s important to keep in mind that venture capitalists only offer terms to 1 or 2% of the deals they see. Be ready to do a lot of pitching. [ <a href="http://mashable.com/2011/06/10/raise-funds-startup/">http://mashable.com/2011/06/10/raise-funds-startup/</a>&#160; ]
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
