<node COLOR="#00b439" CREATED="1311294266689" ID="ID_1288961888" MODIFIED="1322582955804" TEXT="Irrational Risk Aversion">
<richcontent TYPE="NOTE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Risk aversion basically means that we don&#8217;t like losing our stuff. So, in order to avoid that unpleasant feeling of loss (or temporary sacrifice), we consistently settle for less overall. Even when we stand to create six times more wealth in the long term by starting our own company, we prefer that consistent paycheck today from our employer.
    </p>
    <p>
      [Edwards, Elizabeth (2010-12-15). Startup: The Complete Handbook for Launching a Company for Less (Kindle Locations 124-126). Essential Books. Kindle Edition. ]
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
